				<name type="primary" sortindex="1" value="ATS Utah Beach: D-Day On The Cotentin Peninsula" />
			
						                           
						               													<description>The Advanced Tobruk System (ATS) returns to Normandy for an entirely different experience than the earlier Omaha, Juno and King Red offerings.  Here, there are no enemy positions stationed on high ground, this coastal area being relatively flat with a 4-to-8 foot cement wall along the beach.  Make no mistake, however, the area was heavily defended by the German 919th Grenadiers and 709th Infantry Division. Getting ashore (yes, there is a monster, 48-turn invasion scenario) is only half the battle and tactical simulation fans will enjoy the unique maps depicting the Cotentin Peninsula and the flooded farmland inland from the beach itself.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;What You'll Receive:&amp;#10;16 map panels, each 17x11 inches&amp;#10;11 scenarios, the last being the aforementioned 48-turn affair&amp;#10;A 14-page Battlefield Walkaround with module-specific rules and an extensive historical breakdown&amp;#10;&amp;#10;What You'll Need:&amp;#10;Standard ATS rules and charts&amp;#10;ALL necessary counters including German and American personnel, weapons, AFVs, weapons nests and US Landing craft, either from the Normandy modules you already own or via the special counter set, available separately.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;This version is for owners of the latest ATS OMAHA, ATS UTAH Counter Collection and the ATS Rulebook 2014 and later, plus small and large system markers. Includes Landing Craft Play Aid, 8 scenarios, BW Rules in color and color folio.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
